events.name: Social Coding
events.description: A space for women coders to learn from each other, to practice and discuss learnings with fellow peers. This would be a weekly event of informal space to do coding. So bring your pet projects along or join one of our existing teams/ projects to work on. Featured Projects:https://trello.com/b/kl2BTwil/wwc-sg-social-coding-projects First timers, please read:Newbies Step-by-step Guide Please bring your own laptop. Agenda:6:30p - Registration and Introduce projects7:00p - Break out into groups and Start coding! ^_^8:30p - End session There is no food provided, so please make preparations to grab a bite before you turn up. Also, we recommend to bring your own water bottle along. Psst, this event is intended for ladies only.

events.name: The Cybersecurity Awards 2018 Industry Briefing
events.description:
UPDATE:  Thank you for your interest in support of The Cybersecurity Awards 2018 event.  Registration for the 2nd October 2017 event has been fully subscribed.
A similar event has been planned in the near future and we strongly encourage you to register with Lawrence at lawrence.tan@aisp.sg.  Thank you.

Following up from the announcement of The Cyber Security Awards 2018 by Mr Teo Chee Hean, Deputy Prime Minister and Coordinating Minister for National Security at SICW on 19th September 2017, AISP will be holding an Industry Briefing reference the above on 2nd October 2017 commencing 7:00 pm at:

Association of Information Security Professionals116 Changi Road#04-03 WIS@ChangiSingapore 419718

events.name: Papers We Love #029
events.description:
Paper #1:  Contracts for Higher-Order Functions : https://www.eecs.northwestern.edu/~robby/pubs/papers/ho-contracts-techreport.pdf - Soares Chen

Paper #2: Extensibility for the Masses: Practical Extensibility with Object Algebras : https://www.cs.utexas.edu/~wcook/Drafts/2012/ecoop2012.pdf - Melvin Zhang

-------------------

What was the last paper within the realm of computing/technology you read and loved?

What did it inspire you to build or tinker with? 

Come share the ideas in an awesome academic/research paper with fellow engineers, programmers, and paper-readers.

Lead a session and show off code that you wrote that implements these ideas or just give us the lowdown about the paper (because of HARD MATH!). Otherwise, just come, listen, and discuss.

-----------------

Original Meetup : http://www.meetup.com/papers-we-love
Papers Repo : https://github.com/papers-we-love/papers-we-love
Code of Conduct : https://github.com/papers-we-love/papers-we-love/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
events.location: HackerspaceSG, 344B King George's Avenue, King George's Building, Singapore 208576
